–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
Govert Heijboer PhD MSc (Partner)
Co-CIO of True Partner Capital Advisor, has been active as a market maker trading in the European and Asian derivatives markets as well as positional trading since 2003. Govert started as a trader/researcher at Saen Options in Amsterdam and rose to become the director of derivatives trading and a member of the executive team in 2007. In 2008 he moved to Hong Kong to set up and assume responsibility for all trading activities in the new Saen Options Hong Kong branch office. Govert holds a PhD in Management Science and an MSc in Applied Physics from the University of Twente, Netherlands. He is a founding partner and has worked on the launch of the True Partner Fund since March 2010.
Govert Heijboer on LinkedIn
–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
Roy van Bakel MSc (Partner)
Riskmanager and CTO of True Partner Capital Advisor, has been a software developer since 2002, and has focused on risk management and proprietary trading software. He started at Sfiss Financial Technology before moving to Saen Options, where he also served as a trader. In 2008 Roy was named CTO Asia at Saen Options and set up a software development branch office in Chengdu, China. Roy holds an MSc in Applied Mathematics, specialized in financial engineering, from the University of Twente, Netherlands. Roy is a founding partner.
Roy van Bakel on LinkedIn
–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
Tobias Hekster MSc (Partner)
Co-CIO of True Partner Capital Advisor, has been actively trading for the past 14 years in various different roles in several markets across the globe. Starting at IMC in 1998 as a pit trader in Amsterdam, Tobias has established the off-floor arbitrage desk, headed the Chicago office in the transition from floor trading to electronic trading and set up the Asian volatility arbitrage desk in Hong Kong. Tobias holds an MSc in Economics and has taught as an Adjunct Associate Professor at the Chinese University of Hong Kong and as an Adjunct Professor of Financial Practice at National Taiwan University.
Tobias Hekster on LinkedIn
–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
Ralph van Put (Partner)
Next to his role as the CEO of True Partner Holding, Ralph is an Adjunct Professor of Finance at the Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK). He has been active in finance since the late 80's. He started his career as a quantitative analyst at the Pacific Investment Research Institute. Soon after that he started his own investment fund. Besides Asset Management he set up a trading software development company in 1995. This firm has been providing technology evolving with the market from floor-based solutions to co-located HFT setups. The last 10 years he was the CEO of a market making and proprietary trading firm active in the global financial markets. Besides his position at the Chinese University of Hong Kong, he lectures as an Adjunct Professor of Financial Practice at the National Taiwan University (NTU) in Taipei. Ralph actively engages prospects and clients and attends global Prime Broker Capital Introduction events.
Ralph van Put on LinkedIn
–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
Jan Cornelissen MSc (Partner)
Senior Portfolio Manager of True Partner Capital, has more than 18 years of experience as a derivatives trader and market maker. He began his career in 1997 with Saen Options as a pit trader in Amsterdam and he quickly rose through the ranks of positions of progressive responsibility. The board of directors elected to transfer him to the US in 1999 to build and operate Saen’s new operation in Chicago, USA. There he directed a team of 11 professional traders, analysts and risk managers. In 2009, he co-founded a long-short relative value-oriented hedge fund which he managed until early 2016. He holds a MSc in economics from Erasmus University in Rotterdam.
Jan Cornelissen on LinkedIn
–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
Remco Janssen BSc (Partner)
Project Manager at True Partner Capital Advisor, has been a software developer since 1988, with strong expertise in the areas of proprietary trading software development, low latency market access, and high frequency trading architectures. In 2008 Remco moved to Chengdu to work for the software development branch of a proprietary trading firm. Besides being a member of the Management Team, he fulfilled roles as a mentor, senior developer and software architect. As of 2014 he has been based in Hong Kong as lead developer and project manager. Remco holds a BSc in Computer Science.
Remco Janssen on LinkedIn
–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––
Jonney Liu BSc
Senior Portfolio Manager of True Partner Capital Advisor, has been active as a flow derivatives trader and market maker in Asian derivative markets since 2007. He started his career on the Exotic Equities desk at Lehman Brothers in London, since then he has held trading positions as a market maker on Asian indices at Saen Options and was a trader managing the Nikkei index derivatives book at Macquarie on the Index Flow desk in Hong Kong. He holds a BSc in Applied Mathemetics from Columbia University. Jonney joined True Partner in March 2012.
Jonney Liu on LinkedIn
